<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,692,1186]" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,489,728,754]" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">Taxonomic relationships</emphasis>
:—Handel-Mazzetti (1936) and Tang (1937) both considered this species as the intermediate between the alternate leaved clade of 
<taxonomicName box="[710,859,764,790]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Polygonatum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="222" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[710,859,764,790]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">Polygonatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the verticillate species, some of which, like this species, have cirrhose leaf apices. This species is similar in appearance and probably closely related to the sympatric 
<taxonomicName authority="(Liu &amp; Hu 1984: 426) Tamura &amp; Ogisu (1997: 951)" authorityName="Tamura &amp; Ogisu" authorityPageNumber="951" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Liu &amp; Hu" baseAuthorityPageNumber="426" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[136,1067,836,863]" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Heteropolygonatum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="4" pageNumber="222" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pendulum">
<emphasis box="[136,476,836,862]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">Heteropolygonatum pendulum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, Z-G &amp; Hu, X-H." box="[491,724,836,863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="222" pagination="426 - 427" refId="ref6518" refString="http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 67381 Leveille, H. (1909) Decades plantarum novarum XXVI. Repertorium specierum novarum regni vegetabilis 7: 383 - 385. Leveille, H. (1912) Decades plantarum novarum XCIII-C. Repertorium specierum novarum regni vegetabilis 11: 295 - 307. Liang, S. Y. (1987) Two new species of Polygonatum Mill. (Liliaceae) from China. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 25: 64 - 66. Liu, Z-G, &amp; Hu, X-H. (1984) A new species of Polygonatum from Sichuan. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 22: 426 - 427. Miller, P. (1754) Gardeners Dictionary Abridged: Containing the Methods of Cultivating and Improving the Kitchen, Fruit and Flower" type="journal article" year="1984">Liu &amp; Hu 1984: 426</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamura, M. N. &amp; Ogisu, M. &amp; Xu, J." box="[738,1067,836,863]" pageId="4" pageNumber="222" pagination="949 - 956" refId="ref6794" refString="Tamura, M. N., Ogisu, M., &amp; Xu, J. (1997) Heteropolygonatum, a new genus of the tribe Polygonateae (Convallariaceae) from West China. Kew Bulletin 52: 949 - 956. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.2307 / 4117821" type="journal article" year="1997">Tamura &amp; Ogisu (1997: 951)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but that species differs in its long falcate leaves, inflorescences held horizontally, and the plants strictly pendent (Tamura 
<emphasis box="[1154,1207,872,898]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">et al</emphasis>
. 1997). 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, S. F." box="[1307,1451,872,898]" pageId="4" pageNumber="222" pagination="39 - 48" refId="ref6261" refString="Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis, pp. 225 - 235. Chen, S. F. (1989) Karyotype analyses of eight species of Polygonatum Mill. Acta Phytotaxonomica Sinica 27: 39 - 48. Floden, A. (2014) A new combination in Polygonatum (Asparagaceae) and the reinstatement of P. mengtzense. Annales Botanici Fennici" type="journal article" year="1989">Chen (1989)</bibRefCitation>
reported a chromosome number and karyotype of this species from Luding, 
<collectingRegion box="[1008,1098,908,934]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
as 2n = 32. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhao, L. H. &amp; S. D. Zhou &amp; X. J. He &amp; Z. X. Wang &amp; Peng, L." box="[1244,1452,908,934]" pageId="4" pageNumber="222" pagination="441 - 451" refId="ref7496" refString="Zhao, L. H., S. D. Zhou, X. J. He, Z. X. Wang, &amp; Peng, L. (2014) A cytotaxonomic analysis of Chinese Polygonatum (Asparagaceae) species. Nordic Journal of Botany 32 (4): 441 - 451. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / njb. 00255" type="journal article" year="2014">
Zhao 
<emphasis box="[1310,1368,908,934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="222">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
reported two additional counts from Kanding which match the previous in number and karyotype. Both studies reported karyotypes that are distinctly bimodal with 5 pairs of longer subterminal chromosomes and the remaining eleven distinctly shorter and metacentric. This species is known from only a few collections all from a limited area along the Dadu River.
</paragraph>
